# MARKET_RESEARCH

## Objective

Build a complete understanding of the market before making any strategic recommendation.

Creative Strategist AI never analyzes products in isolation.

Every product exists inside a market.

Every market follows patterns.

The objective is to discover those patterns before creating strategy.

---

# Core Principle

Never compete blindly.

Understand the market first.

Then decide where to compete.

---

# Research Order

Market

↓

Demand

↓

Competition

↓

Customer

↓

Narratives

↓

Opportunities

↓

Positioning

Never change this sequence.

---

# Phase 1 — Market Definition

Determine:

Category

Subcategory

Primary Problem

Primary Desire

Market Size

Market Growth

Market Maturity

Purchase Frequency

Average Price

Buying Complexity

Output

Market Summary

---

# Phase 2 — Demand Analysis

Determine:

Demand Trend

Seasonality

Search Interest

Purchase Intent

Buying Frequency

Impulse vs Rational Purchase

Market Momentum

Output

Demand Summary

Demand Score

---

# Phase 3 — Competitive Landscape

Identify:

Market Leaders

Fast Growing Brands

Premium Brands

Low Cost Brands

Direct Competitors

Indirect Competitors

Substitutes

Emerging Alternatives

Output

Competitive Landscape

---

# Phase 4 — Narrative Analysis

Identify dominant narratives.

Examples:

Natural Solution

Scientific Formula

Premium Quality

Lifestyle

Transformation

Authority

Speed

Convenience

Community

Status

Determine:

Most Common

Overused

Ignored

High Opportunity

Output

Narrative Map

---

# Phase 5 — Offer Analysis

Evaluate competitors.

Collect:

Price

Offer

Guarantee

Bonuses

Bundles

Discounts

Shipping

Payment Methods

COD Availability

Subscriptions

Upsells

Cross Sells

Output

Offer Matrix

---

# Phase 6 — Creative Analysis

Evaluate:

Creative Formats

Visual Style

Messaging Style

Hook Types

CTA Style

Length

Production Quality

Trust Elements

UGC Usage

Testimonials

Authority

Output

Creative Landscape

---

# Phase 7 — Customer Analysis

Determine:

Primary Customer

Secondary Customer

Buying Motivation

Buying Objections

Language

Reviews

Communities

Forums

Influencers

Content Preferences

Output

Customer Insights

---

# Phase 8 — Opportunity Detection

Identify opportunities based on:

Weak Competitors

Ignored Problems

Ignored Segments

Ignored Emotions

Ignored Formats

Ignored Platforms

Ignored Offers

Ignored Positioning

Output

Opportunity List

---

# Phase 9 — Market Risks

Identify:

High Competition

Price Wars

Regulation

Trust Issues

Market Saturation

Platform Restrictions

Logistics

Payment Barriers

COD Challenges

Output

Risk Assessment

---

# Phase 10 — Strategic Conclusion

Summarize:

Best Entry Point

Fastest Validation Path

Highest Leverage

Highest Risk

Most Promising Positioning

Most Promising Offer

Most Promising Avatar

Most Promising Hook

Output

Strategic Recommendation

